{
  "stem": "21013.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we lived almost at the edge of a palace called the Prince Eugene Belvedere, which had a beautiful garden and park, where we used to go and play.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was like a two-bedroom apartment.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the only thing that was different was the heating method.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had what was called a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's a big stove built with tiles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it looked like a castle sitting in the corner.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And everything else was just like an American apartment, except the building was old.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was built, I would imagine, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in the 1900s, early 1900s.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, I had two sets of grandparents, except my paternal grandparents died when I was one and three years old.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My grandfather was in the same business as my father.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my grandmother was a housewife, because my father was one of 11 children, and so she was busy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of course, they didn't all survive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my maternal grandparents lived in the small town, Lassee that I mentioned before, where my grandfather was what you would call a gentleman farmer.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He owned a lot of land and it was farmed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And during the First World War, my mother was in charge of 80 Russian prisoners of war that worked on the land, because all the Austrian men had to go to war, so they-- they had these prisoners of war come to work for them.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother's brother and my father's brothers, and-- well, everybody in the family, because they took everybody.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, Austria lost the war, was chopped up.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
